The project includes a Picoblze program that will output a menu of options to the users terminal where the user can then select from a list of options. These options include record, play, pause, and delete (audio increase and decrease available on physical buttons on FPGA). This project utilizes the audio codec on the Spartan6 (SM2603), the onboard DDR2 RAM, picoblaze CPU that processes user input to a state, and a finite state machine for the state produced by Picoblaze. For more details, read the readme included.
